data.chText: 蜘蛛网；蜘蛛丝（尤指落满灰尘的旧蛛网）
data.enText: a fine net of threads made by a spider to catch insects; a single thread of this net (usually used when it is old and covered with dirt)

data.chText: 积有灰尘的角落挂着厚厚的蜘蛛网。
data.enText: Thick cobwebs hung in the dusty corners.

data.chText: 他拂去了头发上的蜘蛛丝。
data.enText: He brushed a cobweb out of his hair.

data.chText: 使头脑清醒；使振作精神
data.enText: to help sb start sth in a fresh, lively state of mind

data.chText: 轻快的散步可以使人头脑清醒。
data.enText: A brisk walk should blow the cobwebs away.

means: 蜘蛛丝(尤指落满灰尘的旧蛛网)

tr: a dense elaborate spider web that is more efficient than the orb web
filaments from a web that was spun by a spider
a fabric so delicate and transparent as to resemble a web of a spider

value.def: A cobweb is the net which a spider makes for catching insects.
If something blows or clears away the cobwebs, it makes you feel more mentally alert and lively when you had previously been feeling tired.

example.ex: ...a walk on the South Downs to blow away the cobwebs.
example.tran: 到南唐斯去徒步旅行，让头脑清醒清醒

value.tran: 使人头脑清醒;使人精神振奋
